Issue 2 (ai-client): Rewrote index.ts with generateDialogue, resolveEvent,
generateEpilogue, streamDialogue — all taking GameState directly. Created 5
phase-specific system prompts (prologue, trail, fort, campfire, finale) with
historical context, comedy-first tone rules, and strict JSON response format.

Issue 3 (characters): New schema with Character type (personality as O/C/E/A/N
1-10), createRelationshipMatrix, getRelationshipLabel (10-tier). 20 hardcoded
characters written for the stable with distinctive voices, specific backgrounds,
and hidden traits that create inter-character friction.

Issue 4 (game-engine): Full state machine in state.ts — Phase, ResourceState,
PartyMember, StressTag, EventHistoryEntry, TrailLocation, GameState, GameAction
(11 action types), gameReducer, and useGameState hook with AsyncStorage
persistence. All packages type-check clean.

